00:40:47.580 --> 00:40:51.200
said that we are persons.

00:40:51.200 --> 00:40:56.190
And the Supreme is
a person, and we

00:40:56.190 --> 00:41:00.030
can have a personal
relationship with him.

00:41:00.030 --> 00:41:04.410
Almost all the others, whether
from the Buddhist tradition

00:41:04.410 --> 00:41:08.910
or Hindu tradition, they were
all on the impersonal side.

00:41:08.910 --> 00:41:14.000
That the goal is you just
give up your individuality

00:41:14.000 --> 00:41:18.010
and merge, and become
one with the spirit,

00:41:18.010 --> 00:41:22.620
or disappear into the void.

00:41:22.620 --> 00:41:28.570
And he taught something
very different,

00:41:28.570 --> 00:41:33.190
that you're a person, and
the Supreme is a person,

00:41:33.190 --> 00:41:36.848
and you can have a
relationship with him.

00:41:40.440 --> 00:41:48.470
And that relationship develops
from the moment you understand

00:41:48.470 --> 00:41:53.010
who you are, understand the
jiva-atma and the param-atma,

00:41:53.010 --> 00:41:56.640
and the relationship
between them.

00:41:56.640 --> 00:42:04.700
But there's also a method for
developing that relationship,

00:42:04.700 --> 00:42:13.140
and that is to purify
our consciousness.

00:42:13.140 --> 00:42:15.710
In other words,
this consciousness

00:42:15.710 --> 00:42:17.840
is not something foreign.

00:42:17.840 --> 00:42:21.880
It's not like we're trying to
impose something artificial,

00:42:21.880 --> 00:42:27.320
or that the tradition is trying,
but it's something natural.

00:42:27.320 --> 00:42:33.840
It's like iron is naturally
attracted to a magnet.

00:42:33.840 --> 00:42:38.340
But if it's covered by
rust, it won't be attracted.

00:42:38.340 --> 00:42:43.050
But if you remove the rust, then
it will naturally be attracted.

00:42:43.050 --> 00:42:47.810
So the jiva-atma's naturally
attracted to the param-atma.

00:42:47.810 --> 00:42:49.650
But we're covered with rust.

00:42:49.650 --> 00:42:57.340
Our minds are covered with
so many misconceptions,

00:42:57.340 --> 00:43:02.520
like "I'm the body, and this is
my husband." "This is my wife."

00:43:02.520 --> 00:43:09.476
"This is my car." "This is
my investment portfolio."

00:43:09.476 --> 00:43:15.080
But we are not any
of those things.

00:43:15.080 --> 00:43:18.200
But even though we may
know that in theory,

00:43:18.200 --> 00:43:21.450
we still may be attached
to those things.

00:43:21.450 --> 00:43:24.320
So we really need to
transfer our attachment.

00:43:24.320 --> 00:43:30.180
And this is a very important
point about the time of death,

00:43:30.180 --> 00:43:33.570
that whatever we
are most attached to

00:43:33.570 --> 00:43:38.360
is what we will think of.

00:43:38.360 --> 00:43:45.270
A friend of mine told a story
that he was driving a car,

00:43:45.270 --> 00:43:47.235
and it stalled on
the railway tracks.

00:43:50.432 --> 00:43:51.390
And you know how it is.

00:43:51.390 --> 00:43:56.680
He was fiddling with it,
trying to get it to go.

00:43:56.680 --> 00:43:59.030
And then, he looked
up, and he saw

00:43:59.030 --> 00:44:02.540
the train was just
bearing down on him.

00:44:02.540 --> 00:44:03.800
He thought, this is it.

00:44:03.800 --> 00:44:06.390
It's all over.

00:44:06.390 --> 00:44:13.490
And the train hit,
and he was chanting.

00:44:13.490 --> 00:44:15.820
I didn't mention
that, but that's

00:44:15.820 --> 00:44:23.930
the best process for cleansing,
is a repetition of mantra.

00:44:23.930 --> 00:44:27.150
So he started chanting.

00:44:27.150 --> 00:44:34.890
And at the last moment, he
thought, what will my wife do?

00:44:34.890 --> 00:44:38.000
And then, the train hit, and
he lost his consciousness.

00:44:38.000 --> 00:44:43.000
Of course, he lived to tell
the story, fortunately.

00:44:43.000 --> 00:44:48.110
So we really have
to become attached

00:44:48.110 --> 00:44:51.120
to the param-atma,
which is natural.

00:44:53.770 --> 00:44:59.530
But that'll be done by a
process of removing that rust.

00:44:59.530 --> 00:45:07.260
And that process is
chanting of the mantra.

00:45:07.260 --> 00:45:09.590
And the Vedas
recommend specific--

00:45:09.590 --> 00:45:13.930
but there are so many, and
even in other traditions.

00:45:13.930 --> 00:45:18.460
I used to spend
time in Pakistan.

00:45:18.460 --> 00:45:24.410
And I came across a book there
called "The 99 Names of Allah."

00:45:24.410 --> 00:45:30.460
And that book mentioned that the
best thing a pious Muslim can

00:45:30.460 --> 00:45:35.870
do at the time of death is to
be chanting the name of Allah.

00:45:35.870 --> 00:45:40.590
And the best thing his family
members and loved ones can do

00:45:40.590 --> 00:45:42.940
is be chanting
the name of Allah.

00:45:42.940 --> 00:45:47.000
So if he can't actually chant,
he can at least hear it.

00:45:47.000 --> 00:45:51.670
And the same thing is there
in the Hindu tradition.

00:45:51.670 --> 00:45:54.890
Instead of, say,
"99 Names of Allah,"

00:45:54.890 --> 00:45:59.980
they have "Vishnu sahasranama,"
"1,000 Names of Vishnu."

00:45:59.980 --> 00:46:04.750
it's the same idea, to chant
the name at the time of death,

00:46:04.750 --> 00:46:09.180
or to be surrounded
by people chanting.

00:46:09.180 --> 00:46:12.970
But even then, the mind
is very flickering.

00:46:12.970 --> 00:46:15.345
So we really want to
just be so attached.

00:46:18.350 --> 00:46:20.790
Sometimes there are
stories of mothers.

00:46:20.790 --> 00:46:24.070
Their child is hit by
a car or something.

00:46:24.070 --> 00:46:28.700
And they're just imbued
with superhuman strength.

00:46:28.700 --> 00:46:31.800
They can lift up the
car, the back of the car,

00:46:31.800 --> 00:46:34.030
to get the child out.

00:46:34.030 --> 00:46:36.905
Because of that
attachment, which is good,

00:46:36.905 --> 00:46:38.780
a mother's attachment.

00:46:38.780 --> 00:46:45.410
So if we have that attachment
for the param-atma,

00:46:45.410 --> 00:46:52.820
then-- the "Bhagavad Gita"
gives another example

00:46:52.820 --> 00:46:55.155
that the body is like dress.

00:46:58.270 --> 00:47:00.230
If your mind is
fixed on something,

00:47:00.230 --> 00:47:01.810
you might be changing
your clothes.

00:47:01.810 --> 00:47:03.820
You hardly are not
even conscious of it.

00:47:03.820 --> 00:47:06.030
You're just, OK.

00:47:06.030 --> 00:47:09.440
So that's the real
perfection, when

00:47:09.440 --> 00:47:12.445
we're so attached
to the param-atma

00:47:12.445 --> 00:47:14.770
that the change of
body is like, we've

00:47:14.770 --> 00:47:17.040
fixed on the param-atma
in this body,

00:47:17.040 --> 00:47:20.290
and we'll stay fixed
on the param-atma.

00:47:20.290 --> 00:47:24.020
That's really the perfection.

00:47:24.020 --> 00:47:25.890
AUDIENCE: So as
a word of comfort

00:47:25.890 --> 00:47:28.890
when you lose a
loved one, can you

00:47:28.890 --> 00:47:33.500
think your memories of them--
in fact, part of their soul

00:47:33.500 --> 00:47:35.710
is now part of your soul?

00:47:35.710 --> 00:47:38.710
GIRIRAJ SWAMI: That's
also a very important part

00:47:38.710 --> 00:47:39.896
of this process.

00:47:43.020 --> 00:47:49.000
Yes, our own final
exam is important,

00:47:49.000 --> 00:47:54.710
but dealing with the loss of
loved ones is also important,

00:47:54.710 --> 00:48:02.400
and also helping people who are
grieving for a lost loved one.

00:48:11.260 --> 00:48:18.830
We can certainly remember
the person who's left us.

00:48:18.830 --> 00:48:23.810
And if we understand
that the atma is eternal,

00:48:23.810 --> 00:48:27.270
we'll know that
that person is still

00:48:27.270 --> 00:48:34.900
alive in some other form
and some other place.

00:48:34.900 --> 00:48:43.530
And it is a fact that when
the atma leaves the body,

00:48:43.530 --> 00:48:48.215
it has powers that
were not manifest

00:48:48.215 --> 00:48:49.215
when it was in the body.

00:48:53.340 --> 00:48:55.760
A colleague of mine
mentioned that he

00:48:55.760 --> 00:49:02.930
had a friend who was a
real-- I say "agnostic"

00:49:02.930 --> 00:49:04.800
just to be polite.

00:49:04.800 --> 00:49:06.390
He was really an atheist.

00:49:06.390 --> 00:49:10.185
But I shouldn't even say
that, because it's not

00:49:10.185 --> 00:49:11.560
that one's better
than the other.

00:49:11.560 --> 00:49:16.340
But he was a real skeptic.

00:49:19.390 --> 00:49:26.290
And when his wife left
her body, she visited him.

00:49:26.290 --> 00:49:30.460
And here, this is someone who
had no belief in any of this.

00:49:30.460 --> 00:49:34.890
He though it was all just
in the mind, all just

00:49:34.890 --> 00:49:35.920
wishful thinking.

00:49:38.450 --> 00:49:41.185
And then, he got
back to my colleague

00:49:41.185 --> 00:49:43.600
and told him what happened.

00:49:43.600 --> 00:49:47.600
And he said, you
know, I may have

00:49:47.600 --> 00:49:50.940
to conceded that some of the
things that you've been telling

00:49:50.940 --> 00:49:54.830
me, which I've been rejecting,
may actually be true.

00:49:58.140 --> 00:50:03.520
But if you believe
in prayer, one thing

00:50:03.520 --> 00:50:07.520
that you can do that could
only help your loved one,

00:50:07.520 --> 00:50:11.510
departed loved one, is
pray for that person.

00:50:14.930 --> 00:50:22.370
Again, prayer is something that
can be met with skepticism.

00:50:22.370 --> 00:50:28.530
But there have been real,
controlled experiments

00:50:28.530 --> 00:50:30.570
with patients.

00:50:33.230 --> 00:50:35.325
And none of the patients
knew whether they

00:50:35.325 --> 00:50:37.600
were being prayed for or not.

00:50:37.600 --> 00:50:44.060
It was a double-blind
experiment.

00:50:44.060 --> 00:50:48.690
And the patients that
were being prayed for,

00:50:48.690 --> 00:50:53.780
they really did much
better than the patients

00:50:53.780 --> 00:50:56.510
who weren't being prayed for,
although they had no idea

00:50:56.510 --> 00:51:00.430
that they were being prayed for.

00:51:00.430 --> 00:51:05.570
And so much so, that
the beneficial effects

00:51:05.570 --> 00:51:10.620
of the prayer was greater
than the beneficial effects

00:51:10.620 --> 00:51:13.020
of most of the
medications that had

00:51:13.020 --> 00:51:16.110
been tested in
similar experiments.

00:51:20.210 --> 00:51:23.120
But anyway, that's up to you.

00:51:26.800 --> 00:51:30.240
But certainly, whoever
that loved one is

00:51:30.240 --> 00:51:35.170
is alive somewhere
in some situation.

00:51:35.170 --> 00:51:45.150
And if that person goes
to the spiritual realm

00:51:45.150 --> 00:51:55.040
immediately, or maybe after
another time in the class,

00:51:55.040 --> 00:52:00.840
and you also go there, and
you'll really be reunited.

00:52:00.840 --> 00:52:04.290
It's not a fantasy or
just wishful thinking.

00:52:07.530 --> 00:52:11.030
And some people, as
they approach death,

00:52:11.030 --> 00:52:18.750
it's said that that line
between this world in the next,

00:52:18.750 --> 00:52:21.330
it becomes sort of permeable.

00:52:21.330 --> 00:52:25.840
And things from
beyond the border

00:52:25.840 --> 00:52:27.970
sort of come into
their consciousness,

00:52:27.970 --> 00:52:30.950
and they can have
amazing revelations.

00:52:33.780 --> 00:52:35.220
And there have
been so many books

00:52:35.220 --> 00:52:38.610
now about out-of-body
experiences

00:52:38.610 --> 00:52:40.500
and near-death experiences.

00:52:40.500 --> 00:52:47.142
And so it's possible.

00:52:47.142 --> 00:52:48.600
JAY: Once again,
we'd like to thank

00:52:48.600 --> 00:52:50.830
Giriraj Swami for this
wonderful lecture.

00:52:50.830 --> 00:52:52.980
